    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="401"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4918</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Nicaraguan Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CZDJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cuadra Zavala</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 26.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to communicate to your
                    excellency that I have received cable instructions from the President of
                    Nicaragua in which he directs me to inform you that last night the Congress of
                        <pb facs="0462" n="290" xml:id="pg_290"/> Nicaragua passed a resolution by
                    the terms of which relations have now ceased between the Government of Nicaragua
                    and the Imperial Government of Germany, and which also authorized the Executive
                    of Nicaragua to offer to the Government of the United States, for the use of the
                    present war, the ports and territorial waters of Nicaragua. It affords me
                    personally much pleasure to perform this duty because it not only gives
                    additional proof of the friendship of Nicaragua for the United States, but also
                    because I am glad to see my Government thus aiding in the struggle for liberty
                    and democracy which the United States is now so nobly conducting.</p>
                <p>With renewed assurances [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CZDJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Joaquin Cuadra Z</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >avala</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
